A Section Of Leaders From Kitui County Have Slammed Leaders From Ukambani Region Who Are Opposed To Wiper Party Leader Kalonzo Musyoka’s 2022 Presidential Bid. Led By Kitui Senator Enock Wambua, The Leaders Specifically Told Off Machakos Governor Alfred Mutua Who In The Recent Past Has Been Too Critical Of Musyoka’s Leadership Style In Ukambani.  Elsewhere, Senate Speaker Kenneth Lusaka Has Warned Governors Who Misappropriate Devolved Funds To Be Ready To Carry Their Own Crosses When They Face Prosecution.